This paper deals with motion and task planning for robots, which is a core topic in robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of random geometric graphs, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The modifications proposed in the paper involve assumptions about the smoothness of the boundary, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV).
